static_cast<type>(value)

this syntax can be used to convert numbers to other types

ex.
static_cast<double>(3)
will convert 3 to a double

ex.
static_cast<int>(7.9)
will convert 7.9 to 7
 
rounds down. dont forget

ex.
static_cast<int>(7.9)


constant variables

const double CONVERSION = 4.4;


x = 5;
y = ++5;

x=6, y =6

x = 5;
y = 5++;

x=6, y=5
